<L>__{313. interior, great cabin night}
<A>__{stephen plays a note on his cello}
<C>__{stephen}
<D>__{shall we begin?}
<A>__{jack pauses, gazing into space.}
<C>__{stephen }
<D>__{jack, brother, you're gathering wool.}
<C>__{jack }
<D>__{thinking about their captain. a great seaman, whatever you may say of him. the doctor said he was killed by our first broadside. i'd have liked to talk to him, face to face.}
<C>__{stephen}
<D>__{maybe you did.}
<C>__{jack}
<D>__{what?}
<C>__{stephen}
<D>__{while i was tending the prisoners they told me their doctor died of fever, two weeks ago. there was no doctor on that ship when we boarded it. and i doubt you will find one there now.}
<A>__{jack goes very still. a silence broken only by the sound of water flowing gently past the hull. he looks down at the captain's sword on the table, the thought of a possible final deception flooding through him.}
